t": "(S, Msb, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  In a case of racing, (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He that intervenes between two contending for a stake"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stakes,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S,) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "third horse in a contest for a stake"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stakes;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "if he outstrip, he takes [the stake"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stakes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "if he be outstripped, he is not fined:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K:) the case is this: two men lay two stakes; and then another comes, and starts his horse with the two others, without [laying] a stake; if one of the first two outstrip, he takes the two stakes, and this is lawful because of the third; but if the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muHal~il", "text_ar": "مُحَلِّل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "outstrip, he takes the two stakes; and if he be outstripped, there is no fine for him: he must be a horse of which one is sure that he may outstrip; otherwise it is termed"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qimaArN", "text_ar": "قِمَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and he is also called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daxiylN", "text_ar": "دَخِيلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muHal~il", "text_ar": "مُحَلِّل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in racing is so called because he makes lawful the contest for a stake or stakes, which had otherwise been unlawful. (Msb.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}